## 8. Phase 13 — Data Layout Pivot: AoS to SoA

**Goal:** Refactor the population memory layout from Array of Structures to Structure of Arrays to enable coalesced memory access in all genetic kernels.

### Why This Is the Critical Architectural Step

In the AoS layout, when thread $i$ and thread $i+1$ each read gene $k$ of their respective tours, the hardware sees:

```
Thread 0 → address: base + 0 * n * sizeof(int) + k * sizeof(int)
Thread 1 → address: base + 1 * n * sizeof(int) + k * sizeof(int)
Thread 2 → address: base + 2 * n * sizeof(int) + k * sizeof(int)
...
```

These addresses are separated by `n * sizeof(int)` bytes. For $n = 500$, adjacent threads access memory 2000 bytes apart. The hardware cannot merge these into a single transaction and issues 32 separate 32-byte loads for one warp — **32× the necessary memory traffic**.

In the transposed SoA layout, when all threads read gene $k$:

```
Thread i → address: base + k * N * sizeof(int) + i * sizeof(int)
```

Adjacent threads access adjacent memory. The warp issues a single 128-byte coalesced transaction.

### SoA Layout

```cuda
/* Structure of Arrays: gene-major layout
   pop_cities[k * N + i] = city at position k in tour i */
typedef struct {
    int    *cities;   /* [n_cities * pop_size]   gene-major   */
    double *length;   /* [pop_size]                           */
    double *fitness;  /* [pop_size]                           */
    int     n;        /* cities per tour                      */
    int     N;        /* population size                      */
} PopulationSoA;

/* Access macro */
#define GENE(pop, city_pos, individual)  \
    ((pop)->cities[(city_pos) * (pop)->N + (individual)])
```

### Updated Evaluation Kernel

```cuda
__global__ void evaluate_population_soa(
        const int    *d_cities,   /* gene-major: [n * N] */
        double       *d_lengths,
        double       *d_fitness,
        const double *d_dist,
        int n, int N)
{
    int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
    if (tid >= N) return;

    double length = 0.0;
    int prev = d_cities[0 * N + tid];   /* gene 0 of individual tid */

    for (int k = 1; k < n; k++) {
        int curr = d_cities[k * N + tid];   /* coalesced: all threads read gene k */
        length += d_dist[prev * n + curr];
        prev = curr;
    }
    length += d_dist[prev * n + d_cities[0 * N + tid]];   /* close tour */

    d_lengths[tid] = length;
    d_fitness[tid] = 1.0 / length;
}
```

