## 9. Phase 14 — Device-Side RNG and Genetic Kernels

**Goal:** Move crossover, mutation, and parent selection onto the GPU. Eliminate the last remaining reasons for the population to touch the CPU every generation.

### cuRAND Setup

One `curandState` per individual. Seeding uses a deterministic function of the master seed, individual index, and generation number — ensuring reproducibility without serialization.

```cuda
__global__ void init_rng(curandState *states, uint64_t master_seed, int N) {
    int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
    if (tid >= N) return;
    /* Each individual gets a unique, deterministic stream */
    curand_init(master_seed, tid, 0, &states[tid]);
}
```

### Tournament Selection Kernel

Tournament selection is the only viable parallel selection strategy. It requires no global prefix sums, no inter-thread communication, and assigns one thread per offspring slot.

```cuda
__global__ void tournament_select(
        const double *d_fitness,
        int *d_parent_a, int *d_parent_b,
        curandState *states,
        int N, int k)
{
    int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
    if (tid >= N) return;

    curandState local = states[tid];

    /* Select parent A */
    int best_a = curand(&local) % N;
    for (int i = 1; i < k; i++) {
        int cand = curand(&local) % N;
        if (d_fitness[cand] > d_fitness[best_a]) best_a = cand;
    }

    /* Select parent B (distinct from A) */
    int best_b;
    do { best_b = curand(&local) % N; } while (best_b == best_a);
    for (int i = 1; i < k; i++) {
        int cand = curand(&local) % N;
        if (d_fitness[cand] > d_fitness[best_b] && cand != best_a) best_b = cand;
    }

    d_parent_a[tid] = best_a;
    d_parent_b[tid] = best_b;
    states[tid] = local;
}
```

### Crossover Kernel Notes

OX1 on GPU uses a shared-memory lookup buffer per thread block or a per-thread register bitmask for small $n$. Branch divergence is the main concern: the traversal of parent B is data-dependent.

```cuda
/* For n <= 64: register bitmask avoids shared memory and branch divergence */
uint64_t used = 0ULL;
/* Mark city c as used: used |= (1ULL << c)  */
/* Check if used:        (used >> c) & 1ULL   */
```

For $n > 64$: use `__shared__` boolean array of size $n$, initialized cooperatively if thread block handles multiple individuals.

### Mutation Kernel

Use a single operator per kernel launch. Mixed operators inside one kernel create warp divergence.

```cuda
__global__ void mutate_swap(
        int *d_cities, curandState *states,
        double mut_rate, int n, int N)
{
    int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
    if (tid >= N) return;

    curandState local = states[tid];
    if (curand_uniform(&local) < mut_rate) {
        int i = curand(&local) % n;
        int j = curand(&local) % n;
        /* SoA swap: swap gene i and gene j for individual tid */
        int tmp = d_cities[i * N + tid];
        d_cities[i * N + tid] = d_cities[j * N + tid];
        d_cities[j * N + tid] = tmp;
    }
    states[tid] = local;
}
```

