## 10. Phase 15 — Memory Hierarchy Optimization

**Goal:** Reduce global memory pressure by tiling frequently accessed read-only data into faster memory tiers.

### Distance Matrix Placement Strategy

| Instance Size | Strategy | Memory Tier | Bandwidth |
|---------------|----------|-------------|-----------|
| $n \leq 128$ (~128 KB) | Pin to constant memory | L1/L2 broadcast | ~10 TB/s (broadcast) |
| $128 < n \leq 512$ (~2 MB) | Shared memory tiling per block | On-chip SRAM | ~19 TB/s |
| $n > 512$ | L2-cached global memory | Global + L2 | ~2 TB/s |

### Constant Memory (Small Instances)

```cuda
__constant__ double d_dist_const[128 * 128];   /* 128 KB fits in constant cache */

/* In host setup: */
cudaMemcpyToSymbol(d_dist_const, h_dist, n * n * sizeof(double));
```

All threads in a warp reading the same constant memory address receive it in a single broadcast. Ideal for distance lookups where all threads in a tour-evaluation block access the same entries.

### Shared Memory Tiling (Medium Instances)

```cuda
__global__ void evaluate_population_tiled(
        const int *d_cities, double *d_lengths,
        const double *d_dist, int n, int N)
{
    extern __shared__ double s_dist[];   /* tile of distance matrix */
    int tid = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;

    /* Cooperatively load a tile of the distance matrix */
    int tile_size = blockDim.x;
    for (int i = threadIdx.x; i < n * n && i < tile_size * tile_size; i += blockDim.x)
        s_dist[i] = d_dist[i];
    __syncthreads();

    if (tid >= N) return;

    double length = 0.0;
    for (int k = 0; k < n - 1; k++) {
        int a = d_cities[k * N + tid];
        int b = d_cities[(k + 1) * N + tid];
        length += s_dist[a * n + b];   /* shared memory: ~100× faster than global */
    }
    d_lengths[tid] = length;
}
```

