## 12. Phase 17 — Warp-Level Primitives and Kernel Fusion

**Goal:** Extract the final 10–20% of hardware performance using low-level CUDA intrinsics and reduce kernel launch overhead through fusion.

> **Important calibration.**  Only pursue this phase if profiling shows that `__syncthreads` and shared memory latency are measured bottlenecks. Do not optimize speculatively.

### Warp Shuffle: Replace Shared Memory Reductions

Warp shuffle instructions (`__shfl_sync`, `__shfl_xor_sync`) allow threads within the same warp to read each other's registers directly, bypassing shared memory entirely and eliminating `__syncthreads` overhead.

```cuda
/* Replace this shared-memory reduction: */
s_val[threadIdx.x] = local_val;
__syncthreads();
if (threadIdx.x == 0) result = s_val[0] + s_val[1] + ...;

/* With this warp-shuffle reduction (32 threads, no shared memory): */
double val = local_val;
for (int offset = 16; offset > 0; offset >>= 1)
    val += __shfl_xor_sync(0xFFFFFFFF, val, offset);
/* Lane 0 now holds the warp sum with zero shared memory and zero syncthreads */
```

Apply to: fitness evaluation reduction, 2-opt delta reduction within warps.

### Kernel Fusion Candidates

| Fusion | Benefit | Risk |
|--------|---------|------|
| Crossover + Mutation | One launch instead of two | Increased register pressure |
| Mutation + Evaluation | Evaluate immediately after mutate | Harder to validate separately |
| 2-opt + Evaluation | Avoid re-launching evaluator | Complex kernel; debug carefully |

**Rule:** Only fuse kernels if `nsys` shows that kernel launch overhead (not execution time) is a measured bottleneck. Premature fusion increases register pressure and reduces occupancy.

### Deliverables

- [ ] Warp-shuffle fitness reduction in evaluation kernel
- [ ] Warp-shuffle delta reduction in 2-opt kernel
- [ ] Profiling comparison: fused vs unfused kernels on benchmark suite
- [ ] Register usage report: verify fusion does not hurt occupancy

### Phase Gate

```bash
# Regression must still pass after every intrinsic change
make cuda_test SUITE=regression_gpu   # all Reg-* tests pass

# Occupancy check: fusion must not reduce occupancy below Phase 16 values
ncu --metrics sm__warps_active.avg.pct_of_peak_sustained_active \
    --kernel-name "evaluate_and_mutate_fused" \
    ./ga_cuda_perf --instance medium_500.tsp --pop 2048 --gen 1 --seed 42
